Males of Pseudopoda acuminata sp. n. could be included in the Pseudopoda martensi -group ( Jaeger , 2001). Males of Pseudopoda martensi -group are characterized by: embolus sickle shaped, strongly flattened, and arising in a prolateral position on the tegulum, first bending in a retrolateral direction and then running in a distal direction; small embolic projection present. Females are difficult to distinguish (
Jaeger 2001
).
